Package main.level_editor_components

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    InputModePanel
    InputModePanel is the panel on the top right of the level editor screen that allows the user to select whether they want to edit tiles or starting positions.
    Map
    Map is the map where the user can place navigation tiles of their choosing
    MapSquare
    MapSquare is each of the individual tiles of the map where the user can assign navigation tiles of their choosing
    ResizePanel
    ResizePanel is the panel on the top left that allows the user to resize the map
    SetTileBagPanel
    SetTileBagPanel is the panel in the middle right of the level editor screen that allows the user to input the number of each type of tile in the tilebag
    TileBagComponent
    TileBagComponent is a visual component that renders in SetTileBagPanel.
    TileSelectionPanel
    TileSelectionPanel is a visual component that is rendered in the LevelEditor Scene.
    TileStackPane
    TileStackPane is a visual component that renders within the TileSelectionPanel parent container.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    TileBagComponent.TILE_IMAGE
    An enumerated type that represents the 7 possible types of tile to add to the TileBag, and contains a URL to an image that visually represents that tile on the screen
